67
00:08:27.576 --> 00:08:30.538
[Dog tag chain rattling]

68
00:08:32.706 --> 00:08:35.292
[quiet music]

69
00:09:06.991 --> 00:09:09.368
Vic. Hey, you get any rest?

70
00:09:09.785 --> 00:09:10.661
Nah.

71
00:09:10.744 --> 00:09:11.829
You look like shit.

72
00:09:12.246 --> 00:09:13.205
Thanks.

73
00:09:14.123 --> 00:09:16.333
Could try and get you some
diphenhydramine if you'd like.


74
00:09:16.417 --> 00:09:17.501
I used to use
it to get to sleep

75
00:09:17.585 --> 00:09:19.003
when my mother-in-law visited.

76
00:09:19.086 --> 00:09:20.838
Let's hope it doesn't
come to that.


77
00:09:22.339 --> 00:09:23.632
Something else?

78
00:09:24.008 --> 00:09:25.509
Saw something else in a crate.

79
00:09:25.634 --> 00:09:27.511
Not sure it was supposed
to be in the supply boat


80
00:09:27.678 --> 00:09:28.971
- Yeah, what?
- Bourbon.


81
00:09:29.972 --> 00:09:32.266
No, no, no. I need to
keep my head clear.


82
00:09:32.391 --> 00:09:34.852
Probably better. There's
no diphen out here anyway.


83
00:09:35.269 --> 00:09:37.188
I hear we're both up
for double shifts today.


84
00:09:37.271 --> 00:09:39.607
No, no. I heard we got
new personnel


85
00:09:39.690 --> 00:09:40.900
coming in from Hawaii.

86
00:09:41.275 --> 00:09:42.610
That's what I heard too.

87
00:09:42.735 --> 00:09:44.195
Looks like that's not
happening anymore.


88
00:09:44.278 --> 00:09:46.572
- This is bullshit.
- Talk to your friend.


89
00:09:47.907 --> 00:09:48.991
Maybe I will.

90
00:09:57.833 --> 00:09:58.876
[knocking]

91
00:09:59.668 --> 00:10:01.170
[Jake] Password.

92
00:10:02.046 --> 00:10:03.464
Come on, Jake, it's me

93
00:10:03.839 --> 00:10:06.091
Good luck, Vic. General's
in a bad mood.


94
00:10:06.967 --> 00:10:09.136
- Isn't he always?
- It's worse.


95
00:10:10.638 --> 00:10:12.389
- Worse?
- Just a warning.


96
00:10:13.891 --> 00:10:14.975
Thanks for the tip.

97
00:10:15.726 --> 00:10:16.936
[knocking]

98
00:10:17.019 --> 00:10:18.145
[music on radio]

99
00:10:18.229 --> 00:10:19.271
Password?

100
00:10:22.441 --> 00:10:24.110
I haven't slept for days.

101
00:10:24.235 --> 00:10:26.487
How am I supposed to remember
what the password is?


102
00:10:26.862 --> 00:10:28.239
That's close enough.

103
00:10:35.412 --> 00:10:36.372
Oh wow.

104
00:10:39.500 --> 00:10:41.377
Now this makes me homesick.

105
00:10:45.506 --> 00:10:47.508
Keeps a little
normalcy in my life


106
00:10:47.633 --> 00:10:49.343
In the middle of all
this insanity


107
00:10:56.517 --> 00:10:57.518
Smoke?

108
00:10:58.144 --> 00:10:59.437
Thanks. I quit.

109
00:11:00.521 --> 00:11:01.897
It helps me with my headaches.

110
00:11:03.399 --> 00:11:04.942
I think that's what
they call addiction.


111
00:11:06.068 --> 00:11:07.236
What do they call this.

112
00:11:08.863 --> 00:11:09.905
Bonus?

113
00:11:11.240 --> 00:11:12.491
I'll drink to that.

114
00:11:15.369 --> 00:11:17.204
What can I help you with, Vic?

115
00:11:19.874 --> 00:11:21.542
I just heard that
we're not getting


116
00:11:21.667 --> 00:11:24.295
- new surgeons shipped in.
- I heard the same.


117
00:11:26.255 --> 00:11:29.675
That's a mistake.
We're being overrun in here.


118
00:11:30.801 --> 00:11:32.636
What do you want me
to do about it?


119
00:11:33.846 --> 00:11:34.763
Plead our case.

120
00:11:34.847 --> 00:11:35.848
They're not gonna listen to me.

121
00:11:35.931 --> 00:11:38.309
They put me out here so they don't
have to listen to me anymore.


122
00:11:40.102 --> 00:11:41.771
We're a week late on
the morphine.


123
00:11:43.314 --> 00:11:44.565
Troops are our priority.

124
00:11:47.610 --> 00:11:50.696
Yeah, I, I'm not
getting any sleep.


125
00:11:51.322 --> 00:11:52.323
I'm not the only one.

126
00:11:52.406 --> 00:11:55.409
Everyone's pulling six shifts
without a break.


127
00:11:56.368 --> 00:11:57.828
It's been over a month, Jake.

128
00:12:00.790 --> 00:12:02.291
How's your hand? 
Still shaking?

129
00:12:04.168 --> 00:12:05.169
Not at the moment.

130
00:12:06.170 --> 00:12:08.214
Well, you keep up this schedule,
don't get enough sleep,


131
00:12:08.339 --> 00:12:11.300
it's gonna get worse and you're
not gonna be any good to us


132
00:12:11.383 --> 00:12:12.718
as a surgeon,
let alone a soldier,


133
00:12:12.802 --> 00:12:14.053
if you have to pick up a weapon.

134
00:12:16.764 --> 00:12:18.641
Luckily, as a surgeon,
we don't have to


135
00:12:18.724 --> 00:12:20.226
arm ourselves during battle.

136
00:12:24.939 --> 00:12:25.940
Vic,

137
00:12:27.441 --> 00:12:28.400
I'll do what I can.

138
00:12:29.693 --> 00:12:30.820
- Thanks, Jake.
- Yeah.


139
00:12:34.073 --> 00:12:35.825
You really should start
easing up on that.


140
00:12:37.368 --> 00:12:39.620
I'm getting ready
so I can toast to Jesus


141
00:12:39.703 --> 00:12:40.746
when my time comes.

142
00:12:41.914 --> 00:12:43.249
Isn't that supposed to be
with wine?


143
00:12:43.791 --> 00:12:45.042
[he chuckles]

144
00:12:45.167 --> 00:12:46.085
Who's keeping track?

145
00:12:47.878 --> 00:12:48.796
Vic,

146
00:12:52.925 --> 00:12:53.926
You'll be home soon.

147
00:13:02.393 --> 00:13:03.727
I wish I could say the same.

148
00:13:07.273 --> 00:13:11.986
[opera plays]

149
00:13:14.238 --> 00:13:15.906
[panicked voices]

150
00:13:16.031 --> 00:13:18.159
Secure the patient!
Prepare for surgery.


151
00:13:18.742 --> 00:13:21.120
Roll him in. Prepare
for surgery.


152
00:13:21.245 --> 00:13:22.621
Secure the patient,
secure the patient.


153
00:13:22.705 --> 00:13:24.748
Hold his legs down. Stay still,
Kid.


154
00:13:24.832 --> 00:13:26.125
[nurse shouts]

155
00:13:26.208 --> 00:13:30.921
Oh my god! Oh my god!
My arm! I'm gonna lose my arm!


156
00:13:31.755 --> 00:13:34.842
Just breathe! Stay with me,
stay with me.


157
00:13:34.967 --> 00:13:36.760
I'm gonna lose my arm,
I'm gonna lose my arm!


158
00:13:36.844 --> 00:13:39.138
You're gonna be fine,
you're gonna be fine!


159
00:13:39.388 --> 00:13:40.389
The bastard jumped at me!

160
00:13:40.473 --> 00:13:41.348
What have you got here?

161
00:13:41.432 --> 00:13:43.225
Chopper to his forearm,
ripped it up pretty bad.


162
00:13:43.976 --> 00:13:46.020
Given him more than enough morphine
but he ain't taking to it


163
00:13:46.103 --> 00:13:48.063
- The arm?
- It's hanging on by a thread.


164
00:13:48.147 --> 00:13:49.398
Needs to be amputated.

165
00:13:49.482 --> 00:13:52.193
- What's your name, Buster?
- Adell.


166
00:13:52.276 --> 00:13:54.779
Adell, is that your
first or last name?


167
00:13:54.904 --> 00:13:56.781
First. Last name's Dollins.

168
00:13:56.864 --> 00:13:59.241
Dollins? Where you from?

169
00:13:59.575 --> 00:14:00.701
Paris, Texas.

170
00:14:01.702 --> 00:14:03.871
I got a cousin from
Greensville. You ever been?


171
00:14:04.705 --> 00:14:05.706
Yeah.

172
00:14:05.873 --> 00:14:07.374
Hold him down. 
Secure the legs.

173
00:14:07.458 --> 00:14:09.251
They've got a great
burger joint.


174
00:14:10.836 --> 00:14:11.796
Am I right?

175
00:14:11.879 --> 00:14:14.465
- Yeah, they do.
- Yeah they do, they do, they do.


176
00:14:16.425 --> 00:14:17.718
And those Texas girls?

177
00:14:17.802 --> 00:14:19.345
I mean, the Southern
belle is awesome.


178
00:14:20.054 --> 00:14:21.430
Mine's from Tennessee,
but you know,


179
00:14:21.514 --> 00:14:23.390
you gotta get one of those,
right?


180
00:14:23.474 --> 00:14:24.475
Yeah, yeah.

181
00:14:24.600 --> 00:14:27.394
Southern girls down there. Huh?
Beautiful.


182
00:14:28.938 --> 00:14:30.731
You did good kid, you did good.

183
00:14:30.815 --> 00:14:32.650
You're okay. It's okay.

184
00:14:33.734 --> 00:14:35.861
No, no, no. You're okay.
You're fine. Don't look.


185
00:14:36.112 --> 00:14:38.155
My arm! My arm!

186
00:14:38.656 --> 00:14:40.407
- My arm!
- Get in, get in. Get back in.


187
00:14:40.491 --> 00:14:41.992
Oh my god, what am I
gonna do with one arm?


188
00:14:43.994 --> 00:14:45.871
Right, get him in a room
and get someone


189
00:14:45.955 --> 00:14:47.540
to write a letter back
home for him, all right?


190
00:14:47.748 --> 00:14:49.792
Guys, that's you too. Let's go.

191
00:14:49.875 --> 00:14:52.336
All right. Let's cut a rug,
sugar.


192
00:14:52.920 --> 00:14:56.132
There we go, people.
There we go. Keep it moving.


193
00:15:00.010 --> 00:15:03.180
[airplanes roar past]

194
00:15:18.404 --> 00:15:20.906
[loud explosions]

195
00:15:25.911 --> 00:15:26.871
God!

196
00:16:05.034 --> 00:16:07.244
[men shouting]

197
00:16:07.411 --> 00:16:10.039
[anxious music]

198
00:16:28.140 --> 00:16:29.433
Private.

199
00:16:29.642 --> 00:16:32.019
Up you get. Up you get, soldier.

200
00:16:38.400 --> 00:16:40.903
[quiet music]

201
00:16:56.043 --> 00:16:57.837
Come on, come on, come on!

202
00:16:59.588 --> 00:17:01.549
Camilla, he needs to get
to surgery, now.


203
00:17:01.631 --> 00:17:03.259
We got a gaping
puncture wound here.


204
00:17:03.342 --> 00:17:05.261
Probably a bayonet,
massive bleeding.


205
00:17:05.343 --> 00:17:07.263
What, you and your friend
would like to be alive?


206
00:17:07.346 --> 00:17:09.723
You think? Made you
bored at Staten island.


207
00:17:09.807 --> 00:17:11.600
Gustavo was proceeding
on Los Angeles.


208
00:17:12.142 --> 00:17:16.147
McWeber, Brooklyn.
Go, go, go, go!


209
00:17:18.441 --> 00:17:20.151
[percussive hit]

210
00:17:27.241 --> 00:17:29.201
- Good work.
- Thank you.


211
00:17:29.702 --> 00:17:31.704
Give him some of
my grandfather's vodka.


212
00:17:32.288 --> 00:17:34.123
You smuggling in booze,
young lady?


213
00:17:35.124 --> 00:17:37.209
You haven't had this vodka yet,
have you?


214
00:17:37.585 --> 00:17:38.544
No.

215
00:17:41.297 --> 00:17:42.465
Oh, sorry.

216
00:17:42.798 --> 00:17:44.300
You didn't wake me.

217
00:17:44.675 --> 00:17:47.052
I can't sleep on this god
forsaken island.


218
00:17:47.178 --> 00:17:48.387
Hey, do me a favor.

219
00:17:48.512 --> 00:17:50.890
Go take care of somebody
worse off than me. I'm fine.


220
00:17:51.348 --> 00:17:52.433
- You sure?
- Yeah.


221
00:17:57.354 --> 00:18:00.566
Insomnia's a pretty common
problem around here.


222
00:18:00.858 --> 00:18:02.318
Where'd you ship in from?

223
00:18:02.860 --> 00:18:04.945
Great Britain. Can't
you tell by my accent?


224
00:18:05.070 --> 00:18:06.489
I could tell you're
from the boroughs.


225
00:18:06.572 --> 00:18:08.324
- That's 'cause you're from Brooklyn.
- Yeah.


226
00:18:08.407 --> 00:18:09.867
But judging by your
lack of accent,


227
00:18:09.950 --> 00:18:11.160
you ain't been there in a while.

228
00:18:13.204 --> 00:18:16.123
I went out to California,
graduated from UCLA.


229
00:18:16.582 --> 00:18:18.334
That was my next question.

230
00:18:18.667 --> 00:18:22.838
But hey, I did pick up
little jolly old English


231
00:18:22.963 --> 00:18:25.966
while I was stationed over
there, comes out when I'm mad.


232
00:18:26.300 --> 00:18:29.553
- Yeah? I can't hear it.
- You will.


233
00:18:31.305 --> 00:18:32.431
How's Gustavo?

234
00:18:34.058 --> 00:18:36.310
Another 10 minutes,
he might not have made it.


235
00:18:37.770 --> 00:18:39.855
Leanne's got a good
bedside manner.


236
00:18:39.939 --> 00:18:41.649
He stands a pretty good chance.

237
00:18:41.941 --> 00:18:43.067
That's good.

238
00:18:44.568 --> 00:18:49.573
Oh! Jesus! What do you give
for pain here, Doc, soda pop?


239
00:18:49.698 --> 00:18:51.867
Easy, easy.
You lost a lot of blood.


240
00:18:52.743 --> 00:18:54.954
They're a quarter inch
away from your kidneys.


241
00:18:55.371 --> 00:18:56.747
Yeah. Nice wound to match

242
00:18:56.872 --> 00:18:58.207
the one on the other side,
right?


243
00:18:58.290 --> 00:19:00.459
I saw that. And a whole
bunch of others.


244
00:19:00.543 --> 00:19:02.044
They tell a story, yeah?

245
00:19:02.545 --> 00:19:03.838
Yeah. All from combat?

246
00:19:04.171 --> 00:19:05.673
Hell no, Doc.

247
00:19:05.965 --> 00:19:08.926
Street fights down at the Plaza bar
by Carrington Avenue.


248
00:19:09.009 --> 00:19:09.885
You ain't been there?

249
00:19:10.177 --> 00:19:11.220
Man. Never heard of it.

250
00:19:12.138 --> 00:19:14.598
You don't get out to the forgotten
boroughs too much, now, do you?


251
00:19:14.807 --> 00:19:17.810
I have a minor league
team that isn't very good.


252
00:19:18.769 --> 00:19:20.479
I forgot what they were called.

253
00:19:26.735 --> 00:19:27.987
Staten Island Yankees.

254
00:19:29.321 --> 00:19:31.740
A disgrace to their names' sake.

255
00:19:31.824 --> 00:19:36.120
Hey, wait. Hey, I tell you
what, when we're outta here,


256
00:19:36.203 --> 00:19:38.622
you meet me in my block
in my neighborhood,


257
00:19:38.706 --> 00:19:40.499
and you put your money
where your mouth is.


258
00:19:40.583 --> 00:19:42.626
