No need to apologize, Vic.

328
00:23:41.323 --> 00:23:42.324
That'll be all.

329
00:23:45.369 --> 00:23:46.370
Yes, sir.

330
00:23:49.540 --> 00:23:51.000
- [Vic] Hey Porter.
- [Porter] What?


331
00:23:51.083 --> 00:23:53.210
That intel. When's it
supposed to happen?


332
00:23:53.377 --> 00:23:54.670
I don't know.

333
00:23:54.753 --> 00:23:56.755
I can go back and try to plead
your case to the General.


334
00:23:56.839 --> 00:23:58.132
This ain't no case, buddy.

335
00:23:58.424 --> 00:24:01.677
[Vic] Look. He's having a bad day
and might be a little drunk.


336
00:24:01.760 --> 00:24:03.429
Don't apologize for him, okay?

337
00:24:03.512 --> 00:24:04.972
It's not your responsibility.

338
00:24:06.307 --> 00:24:07.391
[Vic]
So what do we do?


339
00:24:08.976 --> 00:24:10.102
You ever seen combat?

340
00:24:12.271 --> 00:24:14.440
Don't "Oh" me. I'm asking
you a question.


341
00:24:14.607 --> 00:24:15.900
Have you ever been in combat?

342
00:24:15.983 --> 00:24:17.735
Or do you hide behind
your scalpel


343
00:24:17.818 --> 00:24:19.612
and your syringe
full of morphine all day?


344
00:24:19.945 --> 00:24:21.405
Yeah, I did my basic training.

345
00:24:21.530 --> 00:24:24.575
That's not what I asked.
Have you ever seen combat?


346
00:24:27.077 --> 00:24:28.037
No.

347
00:24:30.247 --> 00:24:32.124
Patching up kids from Missouri,

348
00:24:32.666 --> 00:24:35.044
It's a lot different to
witnessing a 50-caliber shell


349
00:24:35.127 --> 00:24:37.838
rip through a man's chest,
and some of these guys


350
00:24:37.922 --> 00:24:40.508
are your friends. The sound.

351
00:24:41.175 --> 00:24:43.385
That sickening crunch
of blood and bone.


352
00:24:43.761 --> 00:24:45.638
The seconds
that feel like hours.


353
00:24:45.763 --> 00:24:47.723
And then you're waiting.
You're just,


354
00:24:48.140 --> 00:24:50.267
you're waiting for the next
bullet to hit you in the back of


355
00:24:50.351 --> 00:24:52.144
your own fucking head
and it's over,


356
00:24:52.311 --> 00:24:53.646
and over, and over again.

357
00:24:55.773 --> 00:24:58.526
I put these kids back
together day in, and day out.


358
00:24:59.151 --> 00:25:01.904
I seen what happens
over and over.


359
00:25:03.280 --> 00:25:04.532
Okay.

360
00:25:04.740 --> 00:25:07.701
But you ain't seen what's
coming, and maybe you can


361
00:25:07.785 --> 00:25:09.870
understand why I'm
so upset with the General.


362
00:25:10.037 --> 00:25:11.997
This guy used to be
a fucking war hero.


363
00:25:12.123 --> 00:25:14.500
Now, he's just a shadow
of his own reputation


364
00:25:14.792 --> 00:25:16.293
when we need him.

365
00:25:17.962 --> 00:25:18.963
So what do we do?

366
00:25:22.842 --> 00:25:24.009
We evacuate, Doc.

367
00:25:26.137 --> 00:25:27.930
To where? What?

368
00:25:28.139 --> 00:25:30.182
We're understaffed and we're
knee-deep in wounded guys.


369
00:25:30.307 --> 00:25:31.475
Some of 'em can't even walk.

370
00:25:31.600 --> 00:25:34.979
Everybody does their part.
Whoever can fight, fights.


371
00:25:36.272 --> 00:25:38.983
[dramatic music]

372
00:25:40.860 --> 00:25:43.737
[distant gunfire]

373
00:25:48.784 --> 00:25:51.078
- [Fukuda] This, this, or this?
- [Soldier] Yeah.


374
00:25:52.705 --> 00:25:54.373
- Are you sure?
- [Soldier] Sure.


375
00:25:58.335 --> 00:26:01.839
Faster, faster. Do it like
your lives depend on it.


376
00:26:01.964 --> 00:26:02.923
Hey, that's fast.

377
00:26:03.007 --> 00:26:05.468
It's not fast enough, Sergeant,
move, sir.


378
00:26:06.469 --> 00:26:09.472
Hey, five bucks if you
kick his ass.


379
00:26:10.514 --> 00:26:13.309
Can you do it?
Can you punch him?


380
00:26:22.526 --> 00:26:24.361
Well, who woke up the devil,
now?


381
00:26:25.529 --> 00:26:27.072
You should be resting.

382
00:26:28.240 --> 00:26:29.575
I, I, I can't.

383
00:26:29.700 --> 00:26:31.994
This is side I sleep on.
It don't feel so good.


384
00:26:36.165 --> 00:26:37.500
I guess that's it.

385
00:26:38.667 --> 00:26:40.586
I guess I really did
die in here.


386
00:26:41.545 --> 00:26:44.423
- Excuse me?
- Oh, ignore him.


387
00:26:44.507 --> 00:26:46.550
He's been rambling on like
that ever since he woke up.


388
00:26:46.842 --> 00:26:51.222
I can't believe what I'm seeing
here right in front of me


389
00:26:53.390 --> 00:26:55.768
must have died and got
my ass sent to heaven.


390
00:26:57.228 --> 00:26:59.647
Oh no. I promise
you're still alive.


391
00:27:00.022 --> 00:27:03.609
Then how come when I look
around, all I see is angels.


392
00:27:04.110 --> 00:27:05.528
That's because you're in hell.

393
00:27:06.570 --> 00:27:08.864
My apologies.
If I offended any of you.


394
00:27:09.115 --> 00:27:11.909
It's okay. It's just too
much morphine.


395
00:27:12.034 --> 00:27:12.993
Not enough.

396
00:27:15.204 --> 00:27:17.039
What happens if I take too much?

397
00:27:17.373 --> 00:27:18.541
Then it's sweet dreams.

398
00:27:22.461 --> 00:27:24.839
At least I won't have
to pick up a gun again.


399
00:27:27.424 --> 00:27:30.678
[slow orchestral music]

400
00:27:32.638 --> 00:27:34.014
Hey, you doing okay?

401
00:27:36.392 --> 00:27:37.393
I think so.

402
00:27:47.069 --> 00:27:48.612
Where'd you say you was from?

403
00:27:51.073 --> 00:27:52.241
Paris, Texas?

404
00:27:53.742 --> 00:27:57.204
Yeah. That's right.
Born and raised.


405
00:28:03.961 --> 00:28:09.258
Soldier named Pete, he's tall,
dark hair.


406
00:28:12.303 --> 00:28:15.389
He said his mom was Cherokee.

407
00:28:17.475 --> 00:28:19.143
We were at Pearl
Harbor together.


408
00:28:20.770 --> 00:28:22.104
He took a bullet for me.

409
00:28:29.779 --> 00:28:31.489
He's from Powderly.

410
00:28:31.572 --> 00:28:34.366
That's right outside Paris,
isn't it?


411
00:28:34.700 --> 00:28:36.869
Yeah, I've heard of Powderly.

412
00:28:37.828 --> 00:28:40.623
- Yeah.
- Population, about a hundred.


413
00:28:43.375 --> 00:28:44.460
Yeah.

414
00:28:47.004 --> 00:28:48.130
That's what he said.

415
00:28:50.007 --> 00:28:51.383
Anyway, you.

416
00:28:54.178 --> 00:28:56.013
You run into him back home,

417
00:29:00.059 --> 00:29:01.894
