00:30:13.924 --> 00:30:15.009
How's that kid doing?

430
00:30:16.760 --> 00:30:18.387
You'll need to narrow it
down if you want an answer


431
00:30:18.471 --> 00:30:19.805
I didn't pull outta my ass.

432
00:30:20.806 --> 00:30:23.142
The Southern boy, the amputee.

433
00:30:25.311 --> 00:30:28.063
Oh, him. Big Tex.

434
00:30:29.607 --> 00:30:31.817
Well, aside from trying to come
to terms with losing an arm,


435
00:30:31.901 --> 00:30:34.111
I'd say he's doing as well
as he can given the situation.


436
00:30:35.070 --> 00:30:37.782
Morphine's, really working
wonders with his inhibitions.


437
00:30:37.907 --> 00:30:39.116
Kid's coming out of his shell.

438
00:30:43.204 --> 00:30:44.246
Who's he flirting with?

439
00:30:44.914 --> 00:30:46.040
Take your pick.

440
00:30:47.458 --> 00:30:49.877
Well, he's out of his league.
He doesn't stand a chance.


441
00:30:50.085 --> 00:30:51.003
He's pretty charming.

442
00:30:51.086 --> 00:30:52.755
You should go watch him
before he passes out again.


443
00:30:52.838 --> 00:30:54.089
From the morphine?

444
00:30:54.173 --> 00:30:55.508
From one of them slugging him.

445
00:30:58.010 --> 00:31:01.180
[loud planes passing]

446
00:31:03.599 --> 00:31:06.435
[distant gunfire]

447
00:31:12.399 --> 00:31:14.443
[glass jingles]

448
00:31:14.568 --> 00:31:17.613
[approaching rumble]

449
00:31:17.738 --> 00:31:20.407
[anxious music]

450
00:31:30.042 --> 00:31:32.545
[army tank rumbling]

451
00:31:35.506 --> 00:31:36.382
[gun cocking]

452
00:31:45.933 --> 00:31:48.144
Major, my weapon!
