Stay with me. Shit!


580
00:45:46.774 --> 00:45:48.776
I told you, you were
wasting your time.


581
00:45:52.196 --> 00:45:55.157
That man had a wife
and a daughter


582
00:45:55.324 --> 00:45:58.202
Everyone has a wife
and a daughter.


583
00:46:00.538 --> 00:46:01.455
You hear me?

584
00:46:01.539 --> 00:46:02.498
Let it go, Vic.

585
00:46:02.790 --> 00:46:04.083
Listen to your friend.

586
00:46:04.208 --> 00:46:06.001
There's gonna be another
wave coming down here.


587
00:46:06.085 --> 00:46:08.170
And we don't want to be
here when that happens.


588
00:46:09.171 --> 00:46:10.673
He's right. We need to move.

589
00:46:17.596 --> 00:46:18.597
Okay.

590
00:46:20.307 --> 00:46:21.976
Let's see if we can
salvage that thing.


591
00:46:22.059 --> 00:46:24.145
-It may come in handy later, okay
-Right away, sir.


592
00:46:24.270 --> 00:46:25.604
Make it happen.

593
00:46:25.729 --> 00:46:27.273
I'm gonna clear the holes.

594
00:46:30.860 --> 00:46:31.986
God dammit.

595
00:46:32.236 --> 00:46:36.949
Here! Come on, hurry up!
Here, here, move! Here!


596
00:46:37.241 --> 00:46:38.617
Come on, come on!

597
00:46:38.701 --> 00:46:40.578
Let's move, move! Hurry! Hurry!

598
00:46:40.661 --> 00:46:41.745
These are too far apart.

599
00:46:41.829 --> 00:46:43.831
We gotta move them closer
together. We gotta fit everybody.


600
00:46:43.914 --> 00:46:46.041
Come on, we gotta have
room for everybody, down.


601
00:46:46.876 --> 00:46:48.252
In a row, like this.

602
00:46:52.590 --> 00:46:53.841
[gun clicks]

603
00:46:58.971 --> 00:47:00.139
[Jake exhales]

604
00:47:00.306 --> 00:47:02.308
[gunshot]

605
00:47:03.809 --> 00:47:05.144
[Jake exhales]

606
00:47:33.255 --> 00:47:36.008
[gunshots]

607
00:47:41.847 --> 00:47:43.182
[rapid gunfire]

608
00:47:57.863 --> 00:47:59.990
[gunshots]

609
00:48:09.708 --> 00:48:11.001
[Jake exhales]

610
00:48:18.259 --> 00:48:19.301
[gunshots]

611
00:48:38.070 --> 00:48:39.405
[baseball bat clatters]

612
00:48:41.574 --> 00:48:44.577
[Jake breathing heavily]

613
00:48:53.210 --> 00:48:54.712
[Jake groans]

614
00:49:05.306 --> 00:49:07.892
[opera music]

615
00:49:55.147 --> 00:49:57.483
[Glass clatters to floor]

616
00:50:52.204 --> 00:50:53.706
[gunshot]

617
00:50:59.462 --> 00:51:00.379
First kill?

618
00:51:11.307 --> 00:51:12.600
Just remember something.

619
00:51:13.100 --> 00:51:14.685
If it wasn't him, it was me.

620
00:51:15.060 --> 00:51:17.229
Then it was you. You got that?

621
00:51:20.107 --> 00:51:21.108
Got it.

622
00:51:24.695 --> 00:51:25.696
Too much caffeine?

623
00:51:28.574 --> 00:51:29.658
I don't know what it is.

624
00:51:29.742 --> 00:51:32.369
It started after I deployed,
I, I can control it.


625
00:51:33.871 --> 00:51:35.206
Thanks for having my back.

626
00:51:35.372 --> 00:51:38.209
I hope to return the favor.
Let's move.


627
00:51:52.640 --> 00:51:56.477
I think, I think I need
a shot of morphine.


628
00:51:56.644 --> 00:51:57.728
Oh.

629
00:51:58.938 --> 00:52:00.022
You have more,

630
00:52:00.731 --> 00:52:02.942
and there won't be any
for the rest of us.


631
00:52:04.360 --> 00:52:07.446
- My nerves.
- Hey, son.


632
00:52:07.947 --> 00:52:08.906
What I tell you?

633
00:52:08.989 --> 00:52:10.991
Nerves ain't gonna do
no good for you around here.


634
00:52:12.451 --> 00:52:14.411
A shot of morphine
will keep me calm


635
00:52:15.037 --> 00:52:18.040
A shot of morphine is
gonna knock you out.


636
00:52:26.173 --> 00:52:29.468
I need you aware,
'cause like Major said,


637
00:52:29.802 --> 00:52:32.680
I need you to have
my front and my back.


638
00:52:35.224 --> 00:52:36.809
Unless I die peacefully.

639
00:52:38.811 --> 00:52:40.104
You not gonna die.

640
00:52:41.355 --> 00:52:44.150
You not going die.
Look at me, son.


641
00:52:45.317 --> 00:52:46.277
What's your name?

642
00:52:46.777 --> 00:52:48.028
Adell Dollins.

643
00:52:48.195 --> 00:52:50.823
Adell Dollins. I like
the name. Adell Dollins.


644
00:52:51.407 --> 00:52:53.993
Repeat after me Adell.
I'm not going die.


645
00:52:54.368 --> 00:52:56.912
- I'm not going to die.
- Ooh, louder, Adell.


646
00:52:57.371 --> 00:52:59.206
- I'm not going die.
- I'm not going die.


647
00:52:59.290 --> 00:53:00.958
- I'm not gonna die!
- I'm not gonna die!


648
00:53:01.041 --> 00:53:02.460
I'm not gonna die!

649
00:53:03.002 --> 00:53:04.462
Yeah, God got a plan

650
00:53:08.674 --> 00:53:10.342
and look what we got here.

651
00:53:19.643 --> 00:53:20.644
Not bad.

652
00:53:24.565 --> 00:53:27.651
- Where you from, kid?
- California.


653
00:53:28.611 --> 00:53:29.820
You should have enlisted.

654
00:53:30.404 --> 00:53:32.573
Could always use a pair
of hands like yours.


655
00:53:34.909 --> 00:53:37.661
- I tried.
- What do you mean, you tried?


656
00:53:41.248 --> 00:53:42.208
And?

657
00:53:48.005 --> 00:53:49.298
[loud explosion]

658
00:53:50.216 --> 00:53:52.009
Jesus Christ, that was close.

659
00:53:53.969 --> 00:53:55.095
Y'all boys ready?

660
00:53:57.681 --> 00:54:00.518
[energetic music]

661
00:54:06.941 --> 00:54:08.067
Hold.

662
00:54:23.874 --> 00:54:26.377
[men shouting]

663
00:54:50.317 --> 00:54:51.318
No!

664
00:54:56.699 --> 00:54:57.783
Porter!

665
00:55:04.248 --> 00:55:06.208
I think it went clean through.
You okay?


666
00:55:06.417 --> 00:55:08.002
I know you're not, let's go.

667
00:55:08.377 --> 00:55:09.962
- Is he good?
- Yeah.


668
00:55:10.337 --> 00:55:12.715
Over the shoulder, big man.
There you go. Let's move.


669
00:55:50.169 --> 00:55:52.379
[in Japanese]

670
00:56:01.806 --> 00:56:03.307
What are you going to do?

671
00:56:36.048 --> 00:56:37.133
[Ava] You're going to die.

672
00:56:45.683 --> 00:56:47.435
Come on, put me down.

673
00:56:50.438 --> 00:56:52.940
-Empty
-Your shoulder,


674
00:56:53.190 --> 00:56:54.275
it's not lethal.

675
00:56:56.277 --> 00:56:57.194
I'm out.

676
00:56:58.863 --> 00:57:00.281
The General's got guns
in his office.


677
00:57:00.364 --> 00:57:01.490
Wait here.

678
00:57:02.241 --> 00:57:04.577
Give me a hand, come on. Up!

679
00:57:10.666 --> 00:57:13.002
[sad music]

680
00:57:21.010 --> 00:57:21.927
Guys.

681
00:57:33.230 --> 00:57:34.398
He went down fighting.

682
00:57:37.777 --> 00:57:38.778
He died a hero.

683
00:57:50.039 --> 00:57:51.081
It's empty.

684
00:57:54.960 --> 00:57:55.961
Same.

685
00:57:58.839 --> 00:58:01.509
I'm gonna lie down guys.
I don't feel so good.


686
00:58:15.106 --> 00:58:16.440
They took everything.

687
00:58:22.738 --> 00:58:23.781
You okay?

688
00:58:27.034 --> 00:58:27.910
No.

689
00:58:30.121 --> 00:58:31.163
No.

690
00:58:34.959 --> 00:58:37.628
So it will be with
the resurrection of the dead.


691
00:58:39.630 --> 00:58:44.343
The body that is sown is
perishable is raised imperishable.


692
00:58:46.303 --> 00:58:49.348
It is sown weak.
It is raised with power.


693
00:58:50.808 --> 00:58:53.436
It is sown and dishonor,
it is raised in glory.


694
00:59:00.276 --> 00:59:02.194
It is sown as a natural body.

695
00:59:04.029 --> 00:59:07.241
It rises as a spiritual body.

696
00:59:09.160 --> 00:59:12.163
If there is a spiritual body,
there is a natural body.


697
00:59:15.374 --> 00:59:16.292
Corinthians.

698
00:59:21.839 --> 00:59:23.716
That verse got me through
a lot of long nights


699
00:59:23.841 --> 00:59:24.967
since I left home.

700
00:59:27.970 --> 00:59:29.305
How long you been here?

701
00:59:32.308 --> 00:59:33.184
You know.

702
00:59:34.143 --> 00:59:35.394
I used to count the days.

703
00:59:37.104 --> 00:59:39.940
Now, I don't remember
the day I shipped out.


704
00:59:41.358 --> 00:59:44.236
The good thing is I don't obsess
over time anymore. I just, uh...


705
00:59:46.071 --> 00:59:47.573
I just wanna get home someday.

706
00:59:49.909 --> 00:59:51.243
Yeah. You and me both.

707
00:59:57.958 --> 00:59:59.710
Boroughs coming together, yeah?

708
01:00:02.171 --> 01:00:03.506
Boroughs coming together.

709
01:00:04.840 --> 01:00:07.009
We ain't that different
after all, are we?


710
01:00:08.177 --> 01:00:09.637
No. No, we're not.

711
01:00:15.726 --> 01:00:17.144
How about them out there?

712
01:00:22.441 --> 01:00:25.945
I figure they're just as scared
as we are, soldiers.


713
01:00:27.404 --> 01:00:28.447
Following orders.

714
01:00:33.744 --> 01:00:34.995
And I quit.

715
01:00:36.580 --> 01:00:37.748
Why deprive yourself, Doc?

716
01:00:37.873 --> 01:00:40.000
It could be your last
night on this earth.


717
01:00:42.670 --> 01:00:44.797
A forgotten borough
finally making some sense.


718
01:00:45.339 --> 01:00:46.924
Hey.

719
01:00:48.759 --> 01:00:50.136
Cuz I'm from Jersey?

720
01:00:52.513 --> 01:00:54.473
[they laugh]

721
01:00:56.308 --> 01:00:58.394
You know how you could tell
somebody's from Jersey?


722
01:00:58.561 --> 01:00:59.520
How?

723
01:01:01.605 --> 01:01:03.607
They never shut
the fuck up about it.


724
01:01:05.109 --> 01:01:06.735
You don't hear me
denying that one.


725
01:01:13.951 --> 01:01:17.830
Sweet Lord. That tastes
good right now.


726
01:01:17.955 --> 01:01:19.373
There you go, see?

727
01:01:19.498 --> 01:01:21.876
Who says people from Jersey
don't have any taste.


728
01:01:21.959 --> 01:01:23.335
[Connor]
Just don't let my wife know.


729
01:01:25.254 --> 01:01:26.839
She'd actually kill me.

730
01:01:27.673 --> 01:01:30.634
She'd say I'm setting
a piss-poor example for my kid.


731
01:01:31.677 --> 01:01:33.095
You got kids, Porter?

732
01:01:36.307 --> 01:01:37.808
Me? No.

733
01:01:39.101 --> 01:01:41.645
- Not that I know of, anyways.
- Oh, is that right?


734
01:01:41.771 --> 01:01:43.647
No, I'm just saying
that I did a lot of traveling.


735
01:01:43.773 --> 01:01:46.609
So you know, I wouldn't be
surprised if there's some


736
01:01:46.734 --> 01:01:48.319
hard-nosed little bastard
running around,


737
01:01:48.402 --> 01:01:49.862
out there somewhere that
looks like me.


738
01:01:51.530 --> 01:01:52.698
How about you?

739
01:01:57.244 --> 01:01:59.830
Me and my wife, Jenny,
We want kids. It's just...


740
01:02:00.956 --> 01:02:02.208
not in the cards yet.

741
01:02:03.250 --> 01:02:04.460
You didn't try before you left.

742
01:02:05.294 --> 01:02:09.173
Oh, like drunk jack rabbits.
It just didn't happen.


743
01:02:10.007 --> 01:02:11.717
It will. Now when it does,

744
01:02:12.384 --> 01:02:14.762
do your best to keep
outta situations like this


745
01:02:14.845 --> 01:02:17.807
'cause this is ain't no
place for no kid.


746
01:02:20.351 --> 01:02:21.936
That's all we can hope for,

747
01:02:22.603 --> 01:02:24.271
that our kids do
better than we do.


748
01:02:25.272 --> 01:02:26.732
That's what I'm
hoping for my boy.


749
01:02:27.441 --> 01:02:28.818
Damn smart kid.

750
01:02:29.777 --> 01:02:32.863
Lot smarter than I was
at his age. Early bloomer.


751
01:02:35.074 --> 01:02:36.617
Now, you just gotta get
him outta Jersey.


752
01:02:37.952 --> 01:02:41.205
At least to UCLA like this
smarmy bastard, right here.


753
01:02:41.288 --> 01:02:42.873
Oh there it is. There it is.

754
01:02:46.877 --> 01:02:50.381
What's the first thing you're
gonna do the day you get back?


755
01:02:50.506 --> 01:02:51.715
Who you're talking to,
me or him?


756
01:02:52.007 --> 01:02:53.509
Whoever fucking answers first.

757
01:02:53.634 --> 01:02:55.010
I don't know, he's your buddy.
You tell me.


758
01:02:55.094 --> 01:02:56.762
Hey, be my guest.

759
01:02:56.971 --> 01:02:59.557
Why, you embarrassed?
You hiding something over there?


760
01:02:59.890 --> 01:03:00.975
I'll get it outta you.

761
01:03:01.058 --> 01:03:02.476
Try it. I'm Irish.

762
01:03:04.437 --> 01:03:05.479
Me?

763
01:03:06.063 --> 01:03:08.065
You know, I never really
thought about it that much.


764
01:03:11.527 --> 01:03:13.070
I'm thinking maybe a ball game.

765
01:03:14.280 --> 01:03:16.073
First pitch of the season.

766
01:03:17.241 --> 01:03:21.162
Smell of that fresh green grass,
the tall beer in my hand,


767
01:03:21.245 --> 01:03:22.538
a beautiful woman on my arm.

768
01:03:23.706 --> 01:03:25.958
One of those New York
stadium hot dogs in my mouth.


769
01:03:26.667 --> 01:03:28.502
Yeah, it's simple.

770
01:03:29.670 --> 01:03:31.338
That's what I look forward to.

771
01:03:31.839 --> 01:03:33.549
Sounds like
the perfect day to me.


772
01:03:35.676 --> 01:03:36.552
How about you?

773
01:03:38.429 --> 01:03:40.222
I'm from Jersey.
You wouldn't like it.


774
01:03:41.557 --> 01:03:42.475
Try me.

775
01:03:44.477 --> 01:03:46.437
Would love to take
my wife and kid out.


776
01:03:47.146 --> 01:03:48.647
Stop in each state.

777
01:03:49.940 --> 01:03:51.108
Show them the country.

778
01:03:52.610 --> 01:03:53.819
Travel.

779
01:03:55.946 --> 01:03:58.032
Show my boy what
his dad was out protecting.


780
01:04:00.451 --> 01:04:01.410
Show him why.

781
01:04:04.163 --> 01:04:05.164
That sounds nice.

782
01:04:06.040 --> 01:04:08.042
Just skip the rest of Jersey
and parts of Connecticut.


783
01:04:08.125 --> 01:04:10.169
Other than that, it's
just fucking beautiful.


784
01:04:10.461 --> 01:04:11.629
I guess so.

785
01:04:15.508 --> 01:04:17.343
I haven't heard
anything in a while.


786
01:04:19.470 --> 01:04:21.472
Maybe we should get him
down with the others.


787
01:04:21.972 --> 01:04:23.933
Wait for the
reinforcements to find us.


788
01:04:25.768 --> 01:04:27.061
That's if anyone comes.

789
01:04:27.770 --> 01:04:30.147
They don't call this
Purple Heart Ridge for nothing.


790
01:04:31.982 --> 01:04:32.942
Let's get outta here.

791
01:04:42.076 --> 01:04:43.786
What do you plan on doing
with that thing?


792
01:04:44.578 --> 01:04:47.331
You ever see the Babe hit
one out of Yankee stadium?


793
01:04:48.165 --> 01:04:49.125
Dozens of times.

794
01:04:59.677 --> 01:05:00.970
Are you good?

795
01:05:03.305 --> 01:05:05.558
As long as there's a nice
piece-of-shit cot


796
01:05:06.142 --> 01:05:07.893
with someone else's
blood smeared in it


797
01:05:07.977 --> 01:05:10.312
waiting for me downstairs,
I'm ready for anything.


798
01:05:11.105 --> 01:05:13.441
Then keep up. Come on.

799
01:05:13.607 --> 01:05:15.526
Guess you don't know
Jersey very well.


800
01:05:30.207 --> 01:05:31.876
[gunshot]

801
01:05:55.775 --> 01:05:56.859
Hey Doc.

802
01:05:57.526 --> 01:06:00.279
It took Williamson 127
home runs in five years.


803
01:06:00.946 --> 01:06:02.656
You think he'll catch the Babe?

804
01:06:02.948 --> 01:06:04.950
I think the Babe's
record's pretty safe.


805
01:06:10.873 --> 01:06:12.208
Let's see what we can do.

806
01:06:17.254 --> 01:06:20.174
[Vic and Porter screaming]

807
01:06:27.723 --> 01:06:29.683
[man screaming]

808
01:06:54.458 --> 01:06:57.503
[Vic breathing heavily]

809
01:06:59.588 --> 01:07:02.424
[Vic screaming]

810
01:07:09.640 --> 01:07:11.392
All right, clear the chamber!

811
01:07:11.475 --> 01:07:14.228
Get out of there, get
out of the way, come on!


812
01:07:14.478 --> 01:07:16.480
Get my bag. Go get someone
to clean it, right now.


813
01:07:16.605 --> 01:07:18.315
Come on. No, no, no, come on.

814
01:07:19.233 --> 01:07:20.443
- [Vic] I could save you.
- No.


815
01:07:20.568 --> 01:07:22.278
Yes. Yes, I can.

816
01:07:22.403 --> 01:07:23.696
No, you can't.

817
01:07:24.280 --> 01:07:25.448
No.

818
01:07:26.866 --> 01:07:28.242
He hit the femoral artery.

819
01:07:30.244 --> 01:07:31.620
It won't take too long now.

820
01:07:34.874 --> 01:07:36.167
Protect them.

821
01:07:40.838 --> 01:07:43.048
No, no, no, no, no.

822
01:07:43.174 --> 01:07:47.011
Vic, make sure my boy gets this.

823
01:07:49.847 --> 01:07:52.099
He's not old enough
to understand it yet...


824
01:07:56.562 --> 01:07:57.897
but he will be.

825
01:08:24.381 --> 01:08:25.673
He was a good man.

826
01:08:29.470 --> 01:08:31.180
They're gonna make it
down here. You know that.


827
01:08:31.262 --> 01:08:32.388
It's just a matter of time.

828
01:08:36.060 --> 01:08:37.394
Then we'll keep fighting.

829
01:08:46.445 --> 01:08:47.946
I'm gonna take the halls.

830
01:08:48.071 --> 01:08:50.574
I'm gonna kill as many
of these guys as I can.


831
01:08:50.699 --> 01:08:52.827
Anybody makes it down here,
it's on you.


832
01:08:53.035 --> 01:08:54.245
I'm coming with you.

833
01:08:58.374 --> 01:08:59.667
If I don't make it back here,

834
01:08:59.749 --> 01:09:01.544
I want you to know
it's been an honor.


835
01:09:02.419 --> 01:09:03.294
Likewise.

836
01:09:06.841 --> 01:09:08.092
You keep an eye on him.

837
01:09:09.843 --> 01:09:10.845
Don't worry.

838
01:09:11.595 --> 01:09:12.637
Got him covered.

839
01:09:13.931 --> 01:09:15.807
You good to hold fort for me,
Private?


840
01:09:17.142 --> 01:09:18.894
Well, we're in luck.

841
01:09:19.352 --> 01:09:21.271
'Cause I just happen
to learn from the best.


842
01:09:22.273 --> 01:09:23.356
Good whiskey.

843
01:09:23.983 --> 01:09:25.943
Great whiskey, two bottles.

844
01:09:26.026 --> 01:09:27.069
You just make it back.

845
01:09:28.945 --> 01:09:30.448
You remember our bet, right?

846
01:09:32.408 --> 01:09:33.868
You still think you can win?

847
01:09:34.243 --> 01:09:35.202
You're damn right.

848
01:09:45.129 --> 01:09:46.964
Loser buys Dodger tickets.

849
01:09:52.845 --> 01:09:53.971
Get the door

850
01:09:55.306 --> 01:09:56.849
[Percussive hit]

851
01:10:00.644 --> 01:10:03.773
[distant explosions]

852
01:10:31.091 --> 01:10:37.848
[Soldier in Japanese]

853
01:11:08.504 --> 01:11:12.007
[shouting men approaches]

854
01:11:14.343 --> 01:11:16.929
[anxious music]

855
01:11:18.430 --> 01:11:19.431
Quiet.

856
01:11:36.615 --> 01:11:37.575
Steady.

857
01:12:02.308 --> 01:12:05.144
[in Japanese]

858
01:12:50.314 --> 01:12:53.067
[gunfire]

859
01:12:59.240 --> 01:13:01.408
[rapid gunfire]

860
01:13:03.077 --> 01:13:04.078
Shit.

861
01:13:19.009 --> 01:13:20.803
[distant shouting]

862
01:13:21.971 --> 01:13:23.055
Steady.

863
01:13:23.180 --> 01:13:24.140
Steady.

864
01:13:24.265 --> 01:13:27.518
[distant shouting continues]

865
01:13:41.574 --> 01:13:42.741
- [explosion outside]
- [nurse gasps]


866
01:13:42.908 --> 01:13:44.243
Steady.

867
01:13:52.543 --> 01:13:55.337
- [door crashes]
- [rapid gunfire]


868
01:14:02.928 --> 01:14:05.931
[Vic screaming]

869
01:14:07.892 --> 01:14:09.477
[man grunts]

870
01:14:29.705 --> 01:14:31.373
[body thudding]

871
01:14:38.297 --> 01:14:40.716
[man screaming]

872
01:14:48.098 --> 01:14:49.809
[pottery shattering]

873
01:14:53.604 --> 01:14:55.272
[table splintering]

874
01:14:57.775 --> 01:14:59.151
[gunshot]

875
01:15:06.909 --> 01:15:09.745
[dramatic music]

876
01:15:09.912 --> 01:15:12.540
- [men screaming]
- [rapid gunfire]


877
01:15:37.815 --> 01:15:39.066
[Porter coughs]

878
01:15:43.529 --> 01:15:44.822
[Porter gasps]

879
01:16:20.608 --> 01:16:23.068
[grenade thunks]

880
01:16:30.910 --> 01:16:33.704
[loud explosion]

881
01:16:35.414 --> 01:16:38.584
[sad music]

882
01:16:52.097 --> 01:16:54.892
[muffled machine gun fire]

883
01:17:10.407 --> 01:17:11.575
This is the last one.

884
01:17:11.700 --> 01:17:12.993
Make it count.

885
01:17:14.495 --> 01:17:16.205
- [men screaming]
- [rapid gunfire]


886
01:18:02.209 --> 01:18:04.545
[rapid gunfire continues]

887
01:18:06.172 --> 01:18:07.089
I'm out!

888
01:18:14.680 --> 01:18:16.140
Good shot, kid.

889
01:18:21.145 --> 01:18:23.147
That's how we do it
in Paris, Texas.


890
01:18:23.814 --> 01:18:24.857
Oh my god!

891
01:18:24.940 --> 01:18:26.233
Please, no!

892
01:18:28.652 --> 01:18:30.279
Don't die!

893
01:18:31.906 --> 01:18:33.365
Come on, come on.

894
01:18:36.243 --> 01:18:37.244
Don't die.

895
01:18:39.497 --> 01:18:42.458
[suspenseful music]

896
01:18:47.463 --> 01:18:48.881
[gunshot]

897
01:18:53.886 --> 01:18:55.137
You did good.

898
01:19:07.441 --> 01:19:12.113
[sad music]

899
01:19:34.593 --> 01:19:36.637
[energetic music]

900
01:19:36.762 --> 01:19:40.266
- [hammer thudding]
- {men yelling]


901
01:19:45.354 --> 01:19:46.897
[he grunts]

902
01:19:49.650 --> 01:19:51.944
[sad music]

903
01:19:53.070 --> 01:19:55.781
And the others?

904
01:19:59.535 --> 01:20:00.578
Is that it?

905
01:20:01.203 --> 01:20:02.204
Is that all?

906
01:20:03.581 --> 01:20:04.874
I'm sure there's more coming.

907
01:20:05.207 --> 01:20:07.501
I don't think we could handle
another wave like that.


908
01:20:09.962 --> 01:20:11.755
Is this everything we had
in the building?


909
01:20:12.506 --> 01:20:14.925
As far as we know, yeah.

910
01:20:16.051 --> 01:20:17.219
[Vic]
Goddamn.


911
01:20:17.970 --> 01:20:19.972
We could use their ammo,
but that won't last the night.


912
01:20:20.097 --> 01:20:21.348
Yeah. That'll buy us some time,

913
01:20:21.432 --> 01:20:22.683
but that's not the solution.

914
01:20:23.225 --> 01:20:24.477
So what now?

915
01:20:25.186 --> 01:20:27.104
We just sit here and die?

916
01:20:35.905 --> 01:20:37.239
Maybe we won't have to.

917
01:20:38.282 --> 01:20:40.242
I don't think that's enough.

918
01:20:41.911 --> 01:20:43.037
It's a flare gun.

919
01:20:45.206 --> 01:20:47.124
Maybe we can get some
reinforcements.


920
01:20:48.584 --> 01:20:49.627
Are you sure?

921
01:20:53.339 --> 01:20:55.716
I'm outta other options.

922
01:20:56.050 --> 01:20:57.510
Where are you gonna do this?

923
01:20:57.676 --> 01:20:58.636
The roof?

924
01:20:59.845 --> 01:21:01.972
No, I think I'd be
a target there.


925
01:21:05.101 --> 01:21:06.143
Maybe around back.

926
01:21:06.227 --> 01:21:08.062
Maybe there's a little
clearing I can go to.


927
01:21:09.814 --> 01:21:11.607
So you just gonna leave us?

928
01:21:12.441 --> 01:21:14.443
Why don't you just wait
till Porter gets back?


929
01:21:19.865 --> 01:21:21.742
I don't think
Porter's coming back.


930
01:21:28.124 --> 01:21:29.208
I'll be right back.

931
01:21:30.543 --> 01:21:32.128
[Sofia] You know
what's out there.


932
01:21:33.712 --> 01:21:34.839
A minefield.

933
01:21:46.976 --> 01:21:48.477
If I'm not back in 20,

934
01:21:49.437 --> 01:21:50.771
you get everybody you can.

935
01:21:51.105 --> 01:21:55.276
You run like hell until you
find someone friendly, okay?


936
01:21:58.946 --> 01:22:00.197
Hopefully, it won't
come to that.


937
01:22:55.836 --> 01:22:56.962
How long has it been?

938
01:22:57.338 --> 01:22:58.714
About two minutes.

939
01:22:59.256 --> 01:23:00.132
That's it?

940
01:23:01.592 --> 01:23:04.220
Time goes by so slow
when there's no gunfire.


941
01:23:04.637 --> 01:23:05.638
Don't worry.

942
01:23:06.972 --> 01:23:08.265
He knows what he's doing.

943
01:23:12.061 --> 01:23:13.521
[percussive hit]

944
01:23:40.965 --> 01:23:42.091
[metallic click]

945
01:24:04.488 --> 01:24:05.531
He can do it.

946
01:24:09.326 --> 01:24:11.078
He talked me through
losing an arm.


947
01:24:13.164 --> 01:24:14.874
He can make it
through a minefield.


948
01:24:30.973 --> 01:24:33.809
[metallic click]

949
01:25:01.253 --> 01:25:04.173
[fire crackling]

950
01:25:45.506 --> 01:25:46.882
[twig snaps]

951
01:25:52.429 --> 01:25:55.432
[Vic yelling]

952
01:26:01.480 --> 01:26:03.274
[fists thudding]

953
01:26:25.671 --> 01:26:26.589
Go!

954
01:26:29.133 --> 01:26:30.009
Go!

955
01:26:31.510 --> 01:26:32.428
Go!

956
01:26:42.646 --> 01:26:44.398
[he grunts]

957
01:27:01.040 --> 01:27:03.876
[Vic screaming]

958
01:27:09.173 --> 01:27:12.051
[flare gun hisses]

959
01:27:28.859 --> 01:27:31.946
Wait, there it is!

960
01:27:33.405 --> 01:27:34.323
He did it.

961
01:27:48.838 --> 01:27:51.507
[Porter] So it will be with
the resurrection of the dead.


962
01:27:52.842 --> 01:27:54.844
The body that is sown
is perishable.


963
01:27:56.053 --> 01:27:57.638
It is raised imperishable.

964
01:27:58.639 --> 01:28:01.809
It is sown weak.
It is raised with power.


965
01:28:02.810 --> 01:28:05.604
It is sown and dishonored,
is raised in glory.


966
01:28:06.939 --> 01:28:08.899
It is sown as a natural body,

967
01:28:10.317 --> 01:28:13.529
it rises as a spiritual body.

968
01:28:16.240 --> 01:28:19.452
If there is a spiritual body,
there is a natural body.


969
01:28:22.705 --> 01:28:26.750
[sad music]

970
01:28:43.684 --> 01:28:46.145
[inaudible speech]

